Subject: RE: [VB] Thanks to the list for the "Hoover bit" lead

That is what this piece is known as since Mr. Hoover expounded at length on
it's virtues relative to the lifespan of your aircooled T1 engine.  Try
this:

www.thingtech.com/Images/hooverbit.jpg

Funny thing is that right after posting the info below I went to get some
tin welded up for a T4 cooler conversion and had some time to kill while
waiting for it to be done.  Of course I went up the street to the Oakland
Pick and Pull junkyard and while there what do I find?  Why a long block
that someone had pulled from a '67 beetle.  It had the doghouse setup and
the really funny part is that someone took the shroud and all the tin but
left a perfect Hoover bit:)  It also had a really nice breather with the
drip tube that I might get tomorrow when I finish pulling out the rest of a
BA6 heater that was in an aircooled Westy Vanagon.  Sometimes you just have
a really good day at the bone yard.

Thomas

BTW, anybody need a BA6?

